	<div class="main">
		<div class="main-content">
			<div class="book-header">
				<div class="vers-view-type">
					<a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20170621221350/http://catholicbible.online/knox/OT/1_Kgs/7077?vers_inline=1"><img src="https://web.archive.org/web/20170621221350im_/http://catholicbible.online/assets/img/para.jpg" alt=""/></a>					<a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20170621221350/http://catholicbible.online/knox/OT/1_Kgs/7077?comments_open=1"><img src="https://web.archive.org/web/20170621221350im_/http://catholicbible.online/assets/img/C-off.gif" alt=""/></a>				</div>
				<div class="bible-name">The Holy Bible – Knox Translation</div>
				<div class="book-name">The First Book of Kings </div>
				<div class="act-chapter">
					<div class="prev-chapter"><a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20170621221350/http://catholicbible.online/knox/OT/1_Kgs/7076">&lt; prev</a></div>|
					<div class="chapter">Chapter 3</div>
					|<div class="next-chapter"><a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20170621221350/http://catholicbible.online/knox/OT/1_Kgs/7078">next &gt;</a></div>
				</div>
				<div class="chapters">
					<a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20170621221350/http://catholicbible.online/knox/OT/1_Kgs/ch_1">1</a> <a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20170621221350/http://catholicbible.online/knox/OT/1_Kgs/ch_2">2</a> <a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20170621221350/http://catholicbible.online/knox/OT/1_Kgs/ch_3" class="active">3</a> <a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20170621221350/http://catholicbible.online/knox/OT/1_Kgs/ch_4">4</a> <a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20170621221350/http://catholicbible.online/knox/OT/1_Kgs/ch_5">5</a> <a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20170621221350/http://catholicbible.online/knox/OT/1_Kgs/ch_6">6</a> <a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20170621221350/http://catholicbible.online/knox/OT/1_Kgs/ch_7">7</a> <a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20170621221350/http://catholicbible.online/knox/OT/1_Kgs/ch_8">8</a> <a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20170621221350/http://catholicbible.online/knox/OT/1_Kgs/ch_9">9</a> <a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20170621221350/http://catholicbible.online/knox/OT/1_Kgs/ch_10">10</a> <a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20170621221350/http://catholicbible.online/knox/OT/1_Kgs/ch_11">11</a> <a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20170621221350/http://catholicbible.online/knox/OT/1_Kgs/ch_12">12</a> <a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20170621221350/http://catholicbible.online/knox/OT/1_Kgs/ch_13">13</a> <a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20170621221350/http://catholicbible.online/knox/OT/1_Kgs/ch_14">14</a> <a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20170621221350/http://catholicbible.online/knox/OT/1_Kgs/ch_15">15</a> <a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20170621221350/http://catholicbible.online/knox/OT/1_Kgs/ch_16">16</a> <a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20170621221350/http://catholicbible.online/knox/OT/1_Kgs/ch_17">17</a> <a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20170621221350/http://catholicbible.online/knox/OT/1_Kgs/ch_18">18</a> <a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20170621221350/http://catholicbible.online/knox/OT/1_Kgs/ch_19">19</a> <a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20170621221350/http://catholicbible.online/knox/OT/1_Kgs/ch_20">20</a> <a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20170621221350/http://catholicbible.online/knox/OT/1_Kgs/ch_21">21</a> <a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20170621221350/http://catholicbible.online/knox/OT/1_Kgs/ch_22">22</a> <a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20170621221350/http://catholicbible.online/knox/OT/1_Kgs/ch_23">23</a> <a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20170621221350/http://catholicbible.online/knox/OT/1_Kgs/ch_24">24</a> <a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20170621221350/http://catholicbible.online/knox/OT/1_Kgs/ch_25">25</a> <a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20170621221350/http://catholicbible.online/knox/OT/1_Kgs/ch_26">26</a> <a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20170621221350/http://catholicbible.online/knox/OT/1_Kgs/ch_27">27</a> <a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20170621221350/http://catholicbible.online/knox/OT/1_Kgs/ch_28">28</a> <a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20170621221350/http://catholicbible.online/knox/OT/1_Kgs/ch_29">29</a> <a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20170621221350/http://catholicbible.online/knox/OT/1_Kgs/ch_30">30</a> <a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20170621221350/http://catholicbible.online/knox/OT/1_Kgs/ch_31">31</a> 				</div>
			</div>
						<div class="verses">
									<div id="vers151673" class="vers">
												<div class="vers-no">1</div>
						<div class="vers-content">In those days, when Samuel was ministering to the Lord under Heli’s care, a mes-sage from the Lord was a rare treasure; he would not openly reveal himself.</div>
					</div>
									<div id="vers151674" class="vers">
												<div class="vers-no">2</div>
						<div class="vers-content">One night, Heli lay down to rest where he was wont to lie, his eyes dim now with age and sightless,</div>
					</div>
									<div id="vers151675" class="vers">
												<div class="vers-no">3</div>
						<div class="vers-content">and Samuel was asleep, there in the divine presence, where God’s ark was, with the sacred lamp still burning.</div>
					</div>
									<div id="vers151676" class="vers">
												<div class="vers-no">4</div>
						<div class="vers-content">And the Lord’s call came to Samuel. I am coming, he answered;</div>
					</div>
									<div id="vers151677" class="vers">
												<div class="vers-no">5</div>
						<div class="vers-content">then ran to find Heli, and said, I am here at thy summons. Nay, said he, I never summoned thee; go back and lie down again. So back he went, and fell asleep.</div>
					</div>
									<div id="vers151678" class="vers">
												<div class="vers-no">6</div>
						<div class="vers-content">Then the Lord called Samuel again, and again he rose up and went to Heli, to answer his summons. But still no summons had been given, and he must go back to sleep again.</div>
					</div>
									<div id="vers151679" class="vers">
												<div class="vers-no">7</div>
						<div class="vers-content">Till then, Samuel was a stranger to the divine voice; the Lord had not made any revelation to him.</div>
					</div>
									<div id="vers151680" class="vers">
												<div class="vers-no">8</div>
						<div class="vers-content">But when a third time the persistent call came, and Samuel went to Heli,</div>
					</div>
									<div id="vers151681" class="vers">
												<div class="vers-no">9</div>
						<div class="vers-content">still ready at his command, Heli recognized at last whose voice it was the boy had heard. Go back to sleep, he told Samuel; and if the voice comes again, do thou answer, Speak on, Lord; thy servant is listening. And Samuel went back to his bed and fell asleep.<span class="content-paragraph"><br><br></span></div>
					</div>
									<div id="vers151682" class="vers">
												<div class="vers-no">10</div>
						<div class="vers-content">And the Lord came to his side, and stood there waiting. Then, as before, he called him twice by name; and Samuel answered, Speak on, Lord, thy servant is listening.</div>
					</div>
									<div id="vers151683" class="vers">
												<div class="vers-no">11</div>
						<div class="vers-content">And this was the Lord’s message to Samuel: Here is doom I mean to bring on Israel that shall ring in the ears of all that hear of it.</div>
					</div>
									<div id="vers151684" class="vers">
												<div class="vers-no">12</div>
						<div class="vers-content">For Heli it shall bring fulfilment of all the threats I have uttered against his clan; from first to last, they shall be accomplished.</div>
					</div>
									<div id="vers151685" class="vers">
												<div class="vers-no">13</div>
						<div class="vers-content">Warning enough I gave him, I would pass eternal sentence on that clan of his, for his sons’ wickedness that went ever unchecked;</div>
					</div>
									<div id="vers151686" class="vers">
												<div class="vers-no">14</div>
						<div class="vers-content">and now I have taken an oath against all his line, sacrifice nor offering shall ever atone for their sin.<span class="content-paragraph"><br><br></span></div>
					</div>
									<div id="vers151687" class="vers">
												<div class="vers-no">15</div>
						<div class="vers-content">Samuel slept on till morning, when it was time for him to open the doors of the Lord’s house; and fear withheld him from telling Heli of his vision.</div>
					</div>
									<div id="vers151688" class="vers">
												<div class="vers-no">16</div>
						<div class="vers-content">Then he heard the voice of Heli calling, Samuel, my son Samuel! I am ready at thy command, said he.</div>
					</div>
									<div id="vers151689" class="vers">
												<div class="vers-no">17</div>
						<div class="vers-content">And Heli asked him, What message is it the Lord has sent thee? May the Lord give thee thy due of punishment, and more than thy due, if thou hidest from me any word of the message that was given thee.</div>
					</div>
									<div id="vers151690" class="vers">
												<div class="vers-no">18</div>
						<div class="vers-content">Thereupon Samuel told him all that was said, keeping nothing back from him. It is the Lord, answered he, that has spoken; let him do his will.<span class="content-paragraph"><br><br></span></div>
					</div>
									<div id="vers151691" class="vers">
												<div class="vers-no">19</div>
						<div class="vers-content">Samuel grew up, still enjoying the Lord’s favour, and no word he spoke went unfulfilled,</div>
					</div>
									<div id="vers151692" class="vers">
												<div class="vers-no">20</div>
						<div class="vers-content">so that he became known all over Israel, from Dan to Bersabee, as the Lord’s true prophet.</div>
					</div>
									<div id="vers151693" class="vers">
												<div class="vers-no">21</div>
						<div class="vers-content">After this revelation made to Samuel in Silo, the Lord continued to reveal himself there, as he had promised; and when Samuel spoke, all Israel listened.<span class="content-paragraph"><br><br></span></div>
					</div>
							</div>
